version 3.5 + autoreconf

OSC string terminator: Always send ST, but accept either ST or BEL.

   [Thomas Dickey [1]]
   ... in understanding the beginning of Operating System Controls:

   OSC Ps ; Pt ST
   OSC Ps ; Pt BEL

   Using BEL (\007) to end an escape sequence is an anomaly.
   It does not follow the standard (ECMA-48). Operating system controls
   should begin with either ESC ] or 0x9d, and end with ESC \ or 0x9c.

[1] https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/290473
[2] https://github.com/JessThrysoee/xtermcontrol/issues/8

Handle raw read returning -1 and EAGAIN

tcsetattr(3). If no data is available, POSIX permits a read(2)
in noncanonical mode to return either 0, or -1 with errno set
to EAGAIN.
